# Ticket 6 - Unauthorized Port Audit

## Scenario

A Cyber Security Lead requested identification of unauthorized open ports on DMZ-Server2.

## Investigation

### Tools Used

* Nmap
* Linux Socket Analysis

### Commands

```bash
nmap -sV <target>
nmap -p- <target>
ss -tulnp
```

### Findings

Several ports were identified that were not part of the approved port list.

Unauthorized Ports:

```text
21
80
111
139
145
443
666
5489
9000
9001
9999
```

## Root Cause

Multiple services were listening on ports that were not approved by the organization's security policy.

## Resolution

Documented all unauthorized ports in Ticket6.ports.txt and validated the audit.

## Skills Demonstrated

* Security Auditing
* Nmap Enumeration
* Port Analysis
* Security Documentation

